line_2: For us, the sun shall climb the eastern hill;

line_1: From their curst Mouths the dropping Fires distill,
line_2: Enflame the Blood, and shed the spreading Ill.

line_1: Where the dark vapours nightly dews distill,

line_1: From spicy Trees which odourous Gums distil.

line_1: Let me take warning, lesson'd to distill,

line_1: IV.  "GNOMES! YOU then bade dissolving SHELLS distil
line_2: From the loose summits of each shatter'd hill,

line_1: Bade on your sands no night-born dews distil,
line_2: Stay'd with vindictive hands the scanty rill. —

line_1: And showers of tears in blended streams distil;
line_2: Blood from each clotted hair, and horny quill,

line_1: On the bright lake YOUR gelid hands distil
line_2: In pearly showers the parsimonious rill;

line_1: Seeks, where fine pores their dulcet balm distill,
line_2: And sucks the treasure with proboscis-bill;

line_1: Tho' Attic bees each word distil;
line_2: Each thought, tho' bright Invention fill,

line_1: See the silver stream distill!
line_2: When 'tis sun-drove from the hill!

line_2: Nor bloomy vines wave radiant on the hill;

line_2: The sweets that all their waxen storehouse fill.
